UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387882900189
AB  - This paper assesses the impact of major currency realignments in the 1970s on LDC terms of trade. The issue of the appropriate weighting procedure in effective exchange rate calculation is discussed and alternative measures are compared. The evidence suggests that exchange rate realignments in the 1970s had an influence on LDC terms of trade, but one of second-order magnitude. The impact on the structure of incentives and resource allocation is examined and policy implications are briefly discussed.
