VL  - 10
IS  - 2
SP  - 187
EP  - 207
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/04/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(82)90016-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387882900165
AB  - Buffer stock management of agricultural commodities is an intertemporal optimization problem under uncertainty. Stochastic optimal control techniques are presented as a means of solving this problem and then applied to the problem of farmer income support and price stabilization of the rice market in Taiwan. Deterministic results show that the price variation of a free market solution can be substantially reduced with little favoring of one group over another. Operation of a buffer stock under supply uncertainty is shown to generate greater variability in consumer expenditures and producer income than a free market solution.
