AB  - Very little early technical advance effects export expansion or import substitution. Because technological disemployment (that much misunderstood process) accompanies it, that advance increases aggregate income little, but merely concentrates it in fewer hands. Without continuing exogenous increase in aggregate demand, there will be little growth. This thesis is believed basic to understanding of economic growth. Corollaries relate to ‘export-led growth’, population growth, and the trend during growth in the distribution of income.
